The paper discusses off-policy learning algorithms for control problems, which involve modifying the behavior policy over time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
